      "note_no": "15",
      "note": "Evidently a reference to 8:1 - \"All spoils of war belong to God and the Apostle\" - which, as pointed out in note 1 on that verse, implies that no individual warrior can have any claim to the booty obtained in war. Moreover, fighting for the sake of booty contravenes the very principle of a \"war in God's cause\", which may be waged only in defence of faith or liberty (cf. surah 2, note 167), \"until there is no more oppression and all worship is devoted to God alone\" (see 2:193 and the corresponding note 170). It is to these principles, too, that the Prophet's anticipated answer, mentioned in the sequence, refers."
